Hi all, I am struggling to find out how to make a label for checkbox value on the UI for a Boolean I've added. This if for an email template to toggle displaying a section if needed.
 I can get the UI to show a label for the setting, but when you click on it the checkbox has some text which just says "value". How can I change that?

```  {% boolean "enableSection1" label="Enable Section 1", no_wrapper=True, export_to_template_context=True %}

&lt;div style="{% if widget_data.enableSection1.value == false %}display: none;{%endif%}"&gt;
  {% widget_block rich_text "Section1" overrideable=True, label='Section 1 Text Area', no_wrapper=True  %}
    {% widget_attribute "html" %}
    Content
    {% end_widget_attribute %}
  {% end_widget_block %}
  &lt;/div&gt;```
